<br>
Lifeburn kinda sucks, which is why no one bitches about it, other than the necros. Does 4-6k DD +1500 DoT leech, puts the necro at 1hp with a slow 1500hp heal. Right after landing it, necro is usually frenzy summoned and killed.<br>
<br>
Even if they aren't frenzy summoned and killed, there's a huge problem with the DoT leech part of lifeburn stacking. Many times either the mobs buff/debuff slots are full, or there's something lifeburn won't stack with, and the necro can't land lifeburn. Instead, it 'backfires' and the necro dies instantly.<br>
<br>
In addition, lifeburn doesn't crit.<br>
<br>
Oh, and Lifeburn costs 9AAs, as opposed to Manaburn's 5AAs.<br>
<br>
All in all, most necros I know that use it run about a 40% instant casualty rate for their 5-7k damage, assuming it lands.<br>
<br>
